<article lang="en">
    <title>&daps; Quick Start</title>
    <articleinfo>
        <author><firstname>Christopher-Julian</firstname><surname>Zwickl</surname></author>
    </articleinfo>
    <abstract>
        <para> &daps; is a programm that transform your .xml document into a .txt or .html(-single)
            document for example. Of course it is also possible to transform to .pdf , .wiki , .epub
            and .man files. With Daps you can create distributable archives, too. In the following
            you will learn to use the basics of daps. If you want to see more options and functions,
            enter the command: "daps --help". </para>
    </abstract>    
    
    
