    <sect1>
        <title>Install &daps;</title>
        <para>Install &daps; as the following procedure:</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para> Open Yast</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Click on Software Management</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Go to Search</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Search for "daps"</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para> Install "daps" and "daps-docmanager</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title>Transform</title>
        <para> If you want to transform .xml to .pdf for example then use this way to do
            this:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para> Open your console with Alt+F2. Type into this line: console.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para> Enter in your console: "daps -e YOUR_XML_FILE pdf".</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para> Finished. Your .xml file is now a .pdf file.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para> if you want a other format, change the word text into txt, epub, wiki or man. More
        options can you see with the command: "daps --help"</para>
    </sect1>
